<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Camping respawn points is a lamer tactic</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Cogg">Cogg</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 4:36 p.m. 1/5/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Camping respawn points is a lamer tactic<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1921" TARGET=_self>Camping respawn points is a lamer tactic</A> (TheBlack)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Such a situation happened not that long ago near Akanon, with the filthy high elves being very near to the gates. A very exciting battle ensued as soon as the higher level characters in the zone heard of this transgression and came to the gates to defend our town and our inexperienced, with the end result of the elves running for home (at least those that could). Not only were the slain repeatedly killed and looted as they returned for their stuff (punishment for being so bold and brazen), but a good time was had by both races, and I am sure that the unfortunates that got caught in the crossfire will remember the battle longer than they will remember their deaths.

<P>Of course there was some whining from an elf or 2, but hey, I'm a gnome and I think these whiners deserved everything they got! Learn from it and dont think that PvP means free reign! You pays your money and you takes your chances!
<P>&gt; Almost all of us on the PvP server are against this form of
<BR>&gt; lamer tactic. Unless of course you were a complete lamer
<BR>&gt; yourself and were slaughtering newbies of your own race and
<BR>&gt; wantonly looting them. There really is little or no
<BR>&gt; justification for such behavior. Months ago I sent a request to
<BR>&gt; Verant that the default respawn points be moved within range of
<BR>&gt; the guards or placed back inside the towns. No action was taken
<BR>&gt; on this issue to date.
<P>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
